<meta
    desc="Mana Type: Vine"
    status="DRAFT"
><>

<title>Vine Mana<>

<content>
    <section> Introduction <>
        <p>Vine mana is a type of mana which is harvested from the long vines of the jungle. Vine masters
        can ensnare their foes and bind their movements. They can also deliver cracking blows from far away
        and even around obstacles.<>
        <p>Vine mana has an affinity with <a t="#mana_*_leaf">#<> and <a t="#mana_*_poison">#<>.<>

    <section> Caster Types <>
        <heading level="1">Vine Manipulator<>
        <p>Vine <a t="#mana_*_manipulators">manipulators<> can whip about vines to strike and constrict
        their enemies.<>
        <p>In the presence of vines, vine manipulators can use those manipulate those as well to create much
        larger effects.<>

        <heading level="1">Vine Armorers<>
        <p>Vine <a t="#mana_*_armorers">armorers<> wrap themselves in thick layers of vine that can actually deflect
        attacks and also allows extremely fast movement. Vine armor tends to do less on the defensive side, but
        instead is very powerful for attacking foes with all vines in the armor.<>
        <p>In the presence of vines, they can make their armor several layers thicker granting extra defense.<>

        <heading level="1">Vine Animators<>
        <p>Vine <a t="#mana_*_animators">animators<> can create vine elementals to do their bidding. Vine elementals
        wriggle and write into their opponents to grapple and entangle them.<>
        <p>In the presence of vine, vine animators can create much larger and more effective elementals.<>

        <heading level="1">Vine Item Wielders<>
        <p>Vine <a t="#mana_*_itemWielders">item wielders<> wield items that can grab and entagle enemies. Examples
        include vine whips and vine traps.<>
<>
